info.title: AODocs REST API
info.description: The AODocs REST API exposes most of the features of AODocs. It can be used to implement custom applications, third-party integration, bulk tools, or just to experiment with AODocs.

tags.name: domain
tags.description: Lets you manage (list, load, patch, update, add new, delete) domain settings (beta version, subject to change)

parameters.name: activationCode
parameters.description: Code to activate the domain on AODocs

get.description: Lists the audit log events relative to specified filters.

parameters.name: user
parameters.description: Email of the user who triggered the audit log event

parameters.name: scope
parameters.description: Scope of the event (value in 'DOCUMENT', 'FOLDER', 'SECURITY', 'ADMINISTRATION', 'USER' or 'NOTIFICATION')

parameters.name: eventType
parameters.description: Type of the event (consult AODocs support for all values possible)

parameters.name: minDate
parameters.description: From which date to list the audit log events: a timestamp value is expected (milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT)

parameters.name: maxDate
parameters.description: Until which date to list the audit log events: a timestamp value is expected (milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT)

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The maximum number of events per page. (Default: 50)

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

get.description: Checks the status of the domain.

parameters.name: asUser
parameters.description: Email address of the user to check the status with

parameters.name: storageAdmin
parameters.description: Email address of the storage account

parameters.name: standalone
parameters.description: Whether the application is installed as standalone or not

parameters.name: storageAdmin
parameters.description: Email address of the storage account

parameters.name: standalone
parameters.description: Whether the application is installed as standalone or not

get.description: Lists the storage accounts of the domain.
Gets billing status of the domain.

patch.description: Updates billing status of the domain.

get.description: Gets all custom domain configuration flags defined at domain level.

post.description: Updates values of domain level custom configuration flags. Unspecified flags previously defined at domain level will be deleted!
Sets value for the specified custom configuration flag at domain level.

parameters.name: flagName
parameters.description: The name of the configuration flag

delete.description: Deletes the specified custom configuration flag at domain level.

parameters.name: flagName
parameters.description: The name of the configuration flag

get.description: Gets the custom domain configurations with fallback on default value.

parameters.name: flags
parameters.description: The names of the configuration flags

get.description: Lists the users of the domain, whose license expired. (DEPRECATED : Use licensedUsers with status=EXPIRED instead).

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of licensed users per page. (Default: 50)

parameters.name: order
parameters.description: The attribute ('email', 'name', 'lastLogin', 'lastActivity' or 'revokeCooldownDate') used to sort the expired licensed users and the order ('asc' or 'desc'), e.g. 'lastActivity desc'. Default order is: 'revokeCooldownDate asc'.

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

post.description: Method to call before uploading an image to AODocs. The images are visible to the users who can access the library and if present the document.

parameters.name: libraryId
parameters.description: The ID of the library into which the image will be uploaded

parameters.name: documentId
parameters.description: The ID of a document to filter which users can see the image: only users who can see this document will be able to see the image

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the file to be uploaded

get.description: Lists the licensed users of the domain.

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: The status of licenses to search for. (Possible values: ACTIVE, EXPIRED, OVER_DOMAIN_LIMIT. Default: ACTIVE)

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of licensed users per page. (Default: 50)

parameters.name: order
parameters.description: The attribute ('email', 'name', 'lastLogin' or 'lastActivity') used to sort the licensed users and the order ('asc' or 'desc'), e.g. 'lastActivity desc'

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

post.description: Deletes licensed user(s) from the domain.

get.description: Gets a licensed user of the domain by email.

delete.description: Deletes licensed user(s) from the domain.

patch.description: Updates a domain role (keep existing values for not specified fields).

get.description: Lists the security codes of the domain.

post.description: Creates a security code on the domain.

delete.description: Deletes a security code from the domain.

patch.description: Updates a security code on the domain.

get.description: Gets the list of available standard actions for the current domain (Coming soon! This method isn't yet available. It will be made available in a future release).
Lists statistics for a specified entity (domain, storage account or library). The pagination only works for the library statistics.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: The type of the specified entity ('DOMAIN', 'STORAGE_ACCOUNT' or 'LIBRARY')

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of entities per page. (Default: 50)

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: The token for continuing a previous list request on the next page. This should be set to the value of 'nextPageToken' from the previous response.

get.description: Gets statistics for a specified entity (domain, storage account or library).

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: The type of the specified entity ('DOMAIN', 'STORAGE_ACCOUNT' or 'LIBRARY')

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the specified entity

post.description: Creates a storage account for the domain.

get.description: Gets the storage account by email.

parameters.name: storageAccount
parameters.description: The email of the storage account

delete.description: Deletes a storage account from the domain.

parameters.name: storageAccount
parameters.description: The email of the storage account

patch.description: Updates a storage account on the domain.

parameters.name: storageAccount
parameters.description: The email of the storage account

addedBy.description: The user who added the item (read-only field)

addedTime.description: The date/time at which the item was added (read-only field)

name.description: The displayed name of the user

nonGoogle.description: This user is not a google user

thumbnailPictureUrl.description: The URL of the thumbnail picture of the user

configurations.description: The map of custom configurations to apply at this level (consult AODocs team for more information)

configurationFlagValue.description: The value of a custom configuration flag

configurationsFlags.description: The map of custom configurations values for requested flags

accessRestrictionMode.description: The access restriction mode for the domain.

billingType.description: The billing mode: TRIAL, STANDARD, CUSTOM (read-only field)

domainAdmin.description: The email of the G Suite super administrator account

domainType.description: The type of the domain, e.g., GOOGLE_WORKSPACE, MICROSOFT, etc.

libraryCreators.description: The list of users who can create libraries in the domain, if libraryCreatorsSource = SPECIFIC_USERS

libraryCreatorsSource.description: The mode for library creators audience: ANYONE (anyone of the domain or whitelisted), ONLY_SUPERADMINS (only G Suite super administrators), SPECIFIC_USERS (explicit list in 'libraryCreators' field)

limitLibraryAdminAccess.description: Whether administrators of libraries should have a limited access to the library administration page (only applicable for Team Folder and Secured Folder libraries though)

maxSeats.description: The maximum number of licensed users (0 means unlimited) (read-only field)

notify.description: Whether to notify the AODocs super administrators when pool of available licenses gets low

subscriptionId.description: The technical identifier for the subscription to AODocs (read-only field)

superAdmins.description: The list of users who are AODocs super administrators if superAdminsSource = AODOCS

superAdminsSource.description: The mode for super administrators audience: GOOGLE_APPS (implicitely G Suite super admins) or AODOCS (explicit list in 'superAdmins' field)

supportUrl.description: The URL to redirect support request to

whitelistedDomains.description: The list of whitelisted G Suite domains, i.e. users from those domain may access content in your libraries

whitelistedEmails.description: The list of whitelisted Google accounts (gmail, single G Suite account or Google groups of your domain) who may access content in your libraries

aclEntries.description: The list of user/group/field members of the role

id.description: The ID of the role (read-only field)

name_i18n.description: The internationalized name of the role (read-only field)

privileges.description: The list of privileges belonging to predefined role types (read-only field)

type.description: The type of role in the library: LIBRARY (administrators, contributors, readers), DOCUMENT (document creator, version creator), CUSTOM for any role created manually (including predefined roles) (read-only field)

addedBy.description: The user who added the domain to the whitelist (read-only field)

addedTime.description: The date/time at which the domain was added to the whitelist (read-only field)

nonGoogle.description: This domain is not G Suite or Cloud Identity domain

name.description: The displayed name of the group

thumbnailPictureUrl.description: The URL of the thumbnail picture of the group

maxSeats.description: The maximum number of licensed users (0 means unlimited)

addedBy.description: The user email by whom the token has been added (read only)

addedTime.description: The date of when the token was added (read only)

classId.description: The ID of the class when type = FIELD

className.description: The name of the class when type = FIELD

description.description: The description for type in GROUP, ROLE, FIELD

displayName.description: The display name of the user or group, the name of the role (read-only field)

displayName_i18n.description: The display name of the user or group, the internationalized name of the role (read-only field)

thumbnailPictureUrl.description: The URL of the thumbnail picture (especially for users)

type.description: The type of person (user, group, role, field based, domain i.e. everybody)

value.description: The email address if user or group, the ID of the role, the ID of the class/field (ignored if type = DOMAIN)

active.description: Whether the standard action has been activated in the library

async.description: Whether the action will be executed as an asynchronous task (read-only field)

documentationUrl.description: The URL to an external technical documentation

executionContext.description: The permission context in which the action will be executed (Possible values: RUN_AS_SYSTEM, RUN_AS_USER) (read-only field)

fullDescription.description: A more comprehensive (rich-text) description of the purpose and behaviour of the standard action

name.description: The name of the standard action (read-only field)

pictureUrl.description: The URL of the logo for the standard action (expected size is 240x103, with transparent background)

shortDescription.description: A terse description of the purpose of the standard action

type.description: The type of the provided action (Possible values: RELATION_FILTER, RELATION_RENDER, UPDATE, VIEWER, WORKFLOW_TRANSITION) (read-only field)
